# Core Cursor Rules

## Development Environment
- This is a Raycast extension project
- Uses TypeScript and React
- Package manager: npm
- Follow Raycast API conventions and best practices

## Code Quality
- Use TypeScript for all files
- Follow ESLint and Prettier configurations
- Maintain consistent code style across the project
- Use meaningful variable and function names

## Documentation
- Keep README.md updated with feature changes
- Document complex functions and components
- Update CHANGELOG.md for significant changes

## Project Structure
- Source code in `src/` directory
- Assets in `assets/` directory
- Follow Raycast extension structure conventions

## Development Guidelines
- Test functionality before committing
- Keep dependencies minimal and necessary
- Follow semantic versioning for releases
- Maintain backward compatibility when possible
